Section508.N.Errors.msg: If an input error is automatically detected in this form, check that the item(s) in error are identified and the error(s) are described to the user in text.

Section508.N.Labels.msg: Check that descriptive labels or instructions (including for required fields) are provided for user input in this form.

Section508.N.KeyboardNav.msg: Ensure that this form can be navigated using the keyboard and other accessibility tools.

Section508.A.Img.Ignored.msg: Img element is marked so that it is ignored by Assistive Technology.

Section508.C.Colour.msg: Ensure that any information conveyed using colour alone is also available without colour, such as through context or markup.

Section508.D.Linearised.msg: Ensure that content is ordered in a meaningful sequence when linearised, such as when style sheets are disabled.

Section508.D.HiddenText.msg: If content is hidden and made visible using scripting (such as "click to expand" sections), ensure this content is readable when scripts and style sheets are disabled.

Section508.J.Flicker.msg: Check that no component of the content flickers at a rate of greater than 2 and less than 55 times per second.

Section508.K.AltVersion.msg: If this page cannot be made compliant, a text-only page with equivalent information or functionality should be provided. The alternative page needs to be updated in line with this page's content.

Section508.O.SkipLinks.msg: Ensure that any common navigation elements can be bypassed; for instance, by use of skip links, header elements, or ARIA landmark roles.

Section508.P.TimeLimit.msg: If a timed response is required on this page, alert the user and provide sufficient time to allow them to indicate that more time is required.
